[recto] Ad [Addendum] 110. Witt Library. P.B.II. The Seven Acts of Mercy (from Matthew XXV): 1) Benedict Sale, Parke-Bernet, N.Y. 14-III-1951, N° 79, cradled panel, 163/4 x 231/4 in. Signed P. BR.; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. 1) is not II Harrack for Harrich see 2)'; believed to be identical with one recorded in Bénézit, Dictionary des peintres 1924, vol. I, p. 776, as coming from the coll. Harrack of Vienna; [verso] Gal. Harrack, Vienna. exh. St. Lucas Gal. Vienna 1935, N°52, Holz, 42 x 59 cm. Sig. unten rechts P. Brueghel; 3) Henry Schenck-Stainford (U.S.A.) Exh. Antwerp 1930, N° 62, Bois, 43 x 58,5 cm. Signé en bas à droite: P. Braghel [sic]; 4) Sale Fiévez, Brussels, 8 May 1929, N° 32, Bois, 42,5 x57,5 cm au vente Musée Kemps, Anvers, mai 1898, N° 69.
